We have to find ,n(S) + n(P)
S = {x | x is a positive multiple of 3 less than 100}
$\Rightarrow$ S = {3, 6, 9, 12, 15,……, 99}
$\Rightarrow n(S) = \frac {99}{3} = 33$
P = {x | x is a prime number less than 20}
$\Rightarrow$ P = {2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19}
$\Rightarrow$ n(P) = 8
n(S) + n(P) = 33 + 8 = 41
Therefore, answer is 41
